Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Etton, Yorkshire, England":"Etton, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Maud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705202,"age":3,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":14,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":16,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":30,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":32,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Maud was born about 1555, in Yorkshire, England. She married Thomas Lothrop about 1575, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters. She was buried in Etton, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"about 1555–6 January 1588":"umbes 1555–6. jaanuar 1588","1536–1606":"1536–1606","1576–1653":"1576–1653","1578–1628":"1578–1628","1582–1628":"1582–1628","1584–1653":"1584–1653","1587–1628":"1587–1628","1555–1588":"1555–1588","29 July 1576":"29. juuli 1576","6 January 1588":"6. jaanuar 1588","1571":"1571","1582":"1582","20 December 1584":"20. detsember 1584","4 August 1582":"4. august 1582","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1536":"1536","1578":"1578","1588":"1588","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1653":"1653","1576":"1576","about 1578":"umbes 1578","1585":"1585","1584":"1584","about 1555":"umbes 1555","about 1575":"umbes 1575","1628":"1628","1606":"1606","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Etton, Yorkshire, England":"Etton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1555–6 January 1588":"noin 1555–6. tammikuuta 1588","1536–1606":"